P1 - Security, auditability, and operational confidence

Issue P1-01
Title: Add transaction manifest integrity metadata and validation
Scope:
- Add manifest schema version and integrity checksum/hash fields (`src/CloudStorageORM/Infrastructure/CloudStorageTransactionManager.cs`).
- Validate integrity during recovery and fail explicitly on corruption.
- Document operator guidance (`docs/transactions.md`, `docs/troubleshooting.md`).
Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Corrupted or incompatible manifests fail with explicit actionable errors.
- [ ] Valid manifests recover normally.
Test Checklist:
- [ ] Unit tests for checksum mismatch/version mismatch paths.

Issue P1-02
Title: Introduce optional provider-native temporary lock abstraction
Scope:
- Define optional lock contract without forcing provider-specific behavior into unrelated abstractions (`src/CloudStorageORM/Interfaces/StorageProviders/IStorageProvider.cs` or targeted new contract).
- Implement Azure lease strategy and AWS conditional/object-lock strategy behind opt-in capabilities (`src/CloudStorageORM/Providers/Azure/StorageProviders/AzureBlobStorageProvider.cs`, `src/CloudStorageORM/Providers/Aws/StorageProviders/AwsS3StorageProvider.cs`).
- Document capabilities and limitations (`docs/concurrency.md`, `docs/providers.md`).
Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Locking is optional and capability-discoverable.
- [ ] Failure modes are explicit, not silent fallback.
Test Checklist:
- [ ] Unit tests for capability checks and lock lifecycle.
- [ ] Integration tests for lock contention and timeout behavior.

Issue P1-03
Title: Harden security defaults and diagnostics redaction
Scope:
- Redact sensitive option values from debug/info output (`src/CloudStorageORM/Extensions/CloudStorageOrmOptionsExtensionInfo.cs`).
- Add secure endpoint/config validation guidance and guardrails (`src/CloudStorageORM/Validators/CloudStorageOptionsValidator.cs`, `docs/configuration.md`, `SECURITY.md`).
Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Secrets are never emitted in provider/EF debug strings.
- [ ] Validation errors for insecure configuration are explicit and documented.
Test Checklist:
- [ ] Unit tests for redaction and validator behavior.

Issue P1-04
Title: Add audit trail hooks for mutation lifecycle
Scope:
- Introduce pluggable audit sink hooks around create/update/delete/commit/rollback (`src/CloudStorageORM/Infrastructure/CloudStorageDatabase.cs`, `src/CloudStorageORM/Infrastructure/CloudStorageTransactionManager.cs`).
- Add correlation-id propagation through observability surface (`src/CloudStorageORM/Observability/*`).
- Document usage (`docs/CloudStorageORM.md`, `docs/observability.md`).
Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Consumers can capture who/what/when for mutations through extensibility points.
- [ ] Audit hook failure strategy is explicit and configurable.
Test Checklist:
- [ ] Unit tests for hook invocation ordering and payload.

Issue P1-05
Title: Add performance guardrails and telemetry for full scans
Scope:
- Emit telemetry when query execution falls back to broad list/materialize behavior (`src/CloudStorageORM/Infrastructure/CloudStorageQueryProvider.cs`).
- Add query/persistence counters and timings (`src/CloudStorageORM/Infrastructure/CloudStorageDatabase.cs`).
- Document operational thresholds (`docs/query-patterns.md`, `docs/troubleshooting.md`).
Acceptance Criteria:
- [ ] Operators can identify expensive query patterns from logs/traces/metrics.
- [ ] Guidance exists for mitigating scan-heavy usage.
Test Checklist:
- [ ] Unit tests for scan-detection logic.

